issues.body:
In '5.1. More Specific Instructions' the Vocabulary draft mentions the fact that "statements of preferences are general purpose, machine-readable statements cannot override contractual agreements or more specific statements." 

Does this instruction also apply to the attachment document? Or should this instruction be mentioned or referred to in the attachment? 

@martinthomson

comments.body:
@martinthomson yes there is a URL but you need a so-called TIES account to access it. I am about to go for 3 weeks off with too much before Wednesday so I sent you the file directly by email. 

At my return after 20th of August, I will look to help you access, but as well the JCA-AIML could probably send AIPREF a Liaison Statement with the document. ITU cannot work via email as we are under strict Member States rules but apart from the procedure, many things are possible.

I hope this helps you, my goal is simply so that you do not need to reinvent the wheel on any terms you need to get (+ you have the official reference). Any comments welcome.

